This spontaneous report was received from the mother of a 5 year old Caucasian male regarding Ibuprofen 20 
mg/mL Child Berry Suspension. The child had his tonsils and adenoids removed on 13MAR2015. On 13MAR2015, 
he began taking 1.5 teaspoons of the product every six hours for pain. At approximately 1900 on 13MAR2015, the 
child began experiencing stomach pain and cramping. The mother treated the events with Pepto Bismol and 
contacted the childs physician, who reportedly advised her to discontinue the product if the stomach pain and 
cramping continued. Use of the product was discontinued on 17MAR2015, after which the stomach pain and 
cramping resolved. The child has no known drug allergies. No further information is expected.
